history.content:
honestly if you're a sophomore you have a lot of other semesters to take the rest of your upperdivs. Also keep in mind that upperdivs aren't like lowerdivs so there might be a learning curve the first semester you take upperdivs. I would recommend taking 2 and seeing how it goes. You can take more the following semester if you find you need more of a challenge.

___________________________________________
Also, not a good idea to have a busy schedule if you're taking 162.

history.content:
I'm a sophomore who will have taken all the lowerdiv requirements by the end of this semester and really wanted to take some upperdivs. These are the classes that I was interested in, but I'm afraid I shouldn't overwork myself and stick to 3 (or even 2) techs. Out of the classes for my third choice, which one do you recommend would be a good add-on for a SWE intended CS student? 

I wanted to think in terms of time-consumption as well, since I heard 162 and 170 will already drain a lot of time.
history.subject: 162 + 170 + third class (186 vs 126 vs 160 vs 161)?
